  "texts": [
    "Most speech decoding studies have focused on the language-and speech-dominant left hemisphere 27.",
    "However, little is known about decoding speech representations from the right hemisphere.",
    "To this end, we compared left-versus right-hemisphere decoding performance across our participants to establish the feasibility of a right-hemisphere speech prosthetic.",
    "For both our ResNet and Swin decoders, we found robust speech decoding from the right hemisphere (ResNet PCC = 0.790, Swin PCC = 0.798) that was not significantly different from that of the left (Fig. 3a, ResNet independent t-test, P = 0.623; Swin independent t-test, P = 0.968).",
    "A similar conclusion held when evaluating STOI+ (Supplementary Fig. 1b, ResNet independent t-test, P = 0.166; Swin independent t-test, P = 0.114)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Most speech decoding studies have focused on the language-and speech-dominant left hemisphere 27."
  ]
